Texts.Eng: Doors covered in eyes. Don't blink.

Texts.Chs: 叶族人认为大门对叶族人的看法很滑稽，而叶族人则有领土意识。
Texts.Eng: Floran think doors look at Floran funny. Floran feel territorial.

Texts.Chs: 过度夸张的大眼睛装饰门。鲛人喜欢赤裸裸的美丽来表达重要性。
Texts.Eng: Overly dramatic doors decorated with large eyes. Hylotl prefer stark beauty to convey importance.

Texts.Chs: 这些门的眼睛一直盯着我。
Texts.Eng: These doors are keepin' their eyes on me.

Texts.Chs: 这些门看起来不怎么受欢迎，我想这是个双关语。
Texts.Eng: These doors don't look very welcoming. I think that was sort of a pun.

Texts.Chs: 这些门刺骨的目光正在向我挑战，让我敢于进去。
Texts.Eng: These doors' piercing gazes are just daring me to enter.

Texts.Chs: 这双眼睛散发着恶毒的气息，除此之外还有什么可怕的东西呢？
Texts.Eng: These eyes emanate malevolence. What horrors lie beyond?

Texts.Chs: 只要用一只眼睛，这些门就会把世界看成一个一维空间。
Texts.Eng: With just one eye, these doors would see the world as a one dimensional space.
